events.name: GDG Peshawar Launch & Next '19 Extended
events.description:
As you all are aware of our new chapter, GDG Peshawar starting recently, we're excited to invite you all to this launch event including a Cloud Next '19 Extended as well.

It will be a fun-filled event full of tech-geeks, tech-lovers and community builders focused on what GDG Peshawar plans to do for the ecosystem of Peshawar and the whole Khyber Pakhtunkhwa. We will have speakers working in the government, community builders and individuals expert in Google tools such as TensorFlow, Cloud, Firebase, Flutter and Kotlin.

This event is for those who are:
- Geeks
- Technology Lovers
- Web/Software/Mobile Developers
- Software Engineering/Computer Science Students

A surprise session is also planned specifically for the female attendees and that will be announced later. Stay tuned, excited and see you there.

Register here: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdT4uYaI7CtvkCwFUvWtuKjMp-tt1mkI8SgrfTcWaQj4qCvbA/viewform

events.name: DSC Application Drive
events.description:
Google collaborates with university students who are passionate about growing developer communities and supports them with starting student clubs on their campuses. Developer Student Clubs help thousands of student developers learn and work with their communities to solve real-life problems.

This is for those students who still has 2 years left until their graduation.

We invite you to join us at this Application Drive event for an awareness session so we can guide you through the benefits of joining the DSCs and how to apply for it.

Register here for the event: https://forms.gle/UGo2Yr3hKaQebikj9

events.name: I/O Extended 2019 Peshawar
events.description:
Google I/O (Simply I/O) is an annual developers conference hosted by Google to bring together developers from around the globe annually for talks, hands-on learning with Google experts, and the first look at Google’s latest developer products. I/O showcases technical in-depth sessions focused on building web, mobile, and enterprise applications with Google and open sources such as Android, Chrome and Chrome OS, APIs, Google Web Toolkit, App Engine, and more.

I/O Extended events are held around the world for developers to take part in the I/O experience. This year I/O extended event is going to be the biggest one featuring many amazing speakers including experts from Google. This is the opportunity to learn major Google technologies through exclusive sessions and code labs.

The technology/topics we will be featuring for I/O Extended 2019 Peshawar are:

'Kotlin' and 'Flutter'.

Requirements: Bring Charged Laptops

Free refreshments will be served after the event!

#io19 #io19ExtendedPeshawar

upcoming.name: The Art of Public Speaking | Abbottabad
upcoming.description:
What Greek leader Pericles said more than 2,500 years ago is still true today: “One who forms a judgment on any point but cannot explain” it clearly “might as well never have thought at all on the subject.”

No matter you are an entrepreneur, student, professional, or an individual doing job, public speaking skill is highly significant for you to grow. Leaders like Franklin Roosevelt, Billy Graham, Cesar Chavez, Martin Luther King, Ronald Reagan, Hillary Clinton, Barack Obama, and Nelson Mandela are known for how they delivered their thoughts in an impressive manner to the word.

To help you get this leadership skill and become more clear in sharing your thoughts and influencing other, WTM Peshawar is bringing you an interesting and full of fun and learnings Workshop on the Art of Public Speaking in Abbottabad one 31st of August 2019.

PLEASE NOTE THAT WE HAVE LIMITED SPOTS. Make sure to reserve your seat as soon as possible.

Register on: https://forms.gle/B2xVy5xv7qhSW7cM8

Follow us on TWITTER: https://twitter.com/WtmPeshawar

upcoming.name: DevFest Peshawar 2019
upcoming.description:
DevFest Peshawar comes to Peshawar for the first time and we are planning to hold it on 9th November, 2019.

Join developers, students, mentors, and tech companies for the biggest community organized Google Developer Conference in Peshawar. DevFest Peshawar is a community-run, one-day conference aimed at bringing technology enthusiasts and experts together. About 500 people are estimated to attend DevFest, with speakers coming from all over the Country and abroad. The talks will focus on Google technologies along with other emerging technologies such as Android, Flutter, Firebase, Google Cloud Platform, the Mobile Web, Google Assistant, Machine Learning, and more.

DevFest attendees will be able to familiarise themselves with new and emerging technologies, network, socialise, and help to build the growing tech community in Peshawar and Pakistan. Anyone interested in technology is welcome.

Stay tuned for our schedule.

Brought to you, with love, by GDG Peshawar.
